one"},"cache":{"type":"none"},"title":"RPI","header":{"text":{"id":"area","table":"views","field":"area","label":"","relationship":"none","group_type":"group","content":"If you've never heard of the RPI, it stands for <strong>Ratings Percentage Index<\/strong>, and it's a system primarily used by the NCAA to qualitatively rank college basketball teams. It evaluates a team's success by factoring not only the team's record but the strength of that team's schedule and its opponents' schedules.\r\n\r\nThe basic formula goes like this:\r\n25% = Your team's record as a percentage of games won (PCT)<BR>\r\n50% = The win-loss percentage of the teams you have faced so far, collectively (This is the strength of your schedule, abbreviated below as SOS), and<BR>\r\n25% = The win-loss percentage of all the teams who have played all the teams you have played against -- that is, collectively, your opponents' strength of schedule (OSOS).<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nI've actually been doing this for several years but it was more of a hobby and, until last year, I had never officially published these numbers on the NYACSL website. <strong>NOTE: These rankings have absolutely no relevance on the standings or determining which teams advance to the post-season.<\/strong> It's just an interesting resource for all who are statistically-minded to enjoy.\r\n\r\n","format":"1"}},"header_format":"1","header_empty":0,"items_per_page":0,"offset":0,"use_pager":false,"pager_element":0,"style_plugin":"table","style_options":{"grouping":"","override":1,"sticky":0,"order":"desc","columns":{"field_season_rpi1000_value":"field_season_rpi1000_value","field_team_reference_for_stats_nid":"field_team_reference_for_stats_nid"},"info":{"field_season_rpi1000_value":{"sortable":0,"separator":""},"field_team_reference_for_stats_nid":{"separator":""}},"default":"field_season_rpi1000_value"},"row_plugin":"fields","row_options":[],"query":{"type":"views_query","options":[]}}},"page_1":{"db_table":"views_display","vid":"13","id":"page_1","display_title":"Page","display_plugin":"page","position":"2","display_options":{"sorts":{"field_season_rpi_value":{"order":"DESC","delta":-1,"id":"field_season_rpi_value","table":"node_data_field_season_rpi","field":"field_season_rpi_value","override":{"button":"Use you've never heard of the RPI, it stands for <strong>Ratings Percentage Index<\/strong>, and it's a system primarily used by the NCAA to qualitatively rank college basketball teams. It evaluates a team's success by factoring not only the team's record but the strength of that team's schedule and its opponents' schedules.\r\n\r\nThe basic formula goes like this:\r\n25% = Your team's record as a percentage of games won (PCT)<BR>\r\n50% = The win-loss percentage of the teams you have faced so far, collectively (This is the strength of your schedule, abbreviated below as SOS), and<BR>\r\n25% = The win-loss percentage of all the teams who have played all the teams you have played against -- that is, collectively, your opponents' strength of schedule (OSOS).<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nI've actually been doing this for several years but it was more of a hobby and, until last year, I had never officially published these numbers on the NYACSL website. <strong>NOTE: These rankings have absolutely no relevance on the standings or determining which teams advance to the post-season.<\/strong> It's just an interesting resource for all who are statistically-minded to you've never heard of the RPI, it stands for <strong>Ratings Percentage Index<\/strong>, and it's a system primarily used by the NCAA to qualitatively rank college basketball teams. It evaluates a team's success by factoring not only the team's record but the strength of that team's schedule and its opponents' schedules.\r\n\r\nThe basic formula goes like this:\r\n25% = Your team's record as a percentage of games won (PCT)<BR>\r\n50% = The win-loss percentage of the teams you have faced so far, collectively (This is the strength of your schedule, abbreviated below as SOS), and<BR>\r\n25% = The win-loss percentage of all the teams who have played all the teams you have played against -- that is, collectively, your opponents' strength of schedule (OSOS).<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nI've actually been doing this for several years but it was more of a hobby and, until last year, I had never officially published these numbers on the NYACSL website. <strong>NOTE: These rankings have absolutely no relevance on the standings or determining which teams advance to the post-season.<\/strong> It's just an interesting resource for all who are statistically-minded to enjoy.\r\n\r\n","footer":[],"empty":[],"relationships":{"field_team_reference_for_stats_nid":{"label":"Company\/Team","required":0,"delta":-1,"id":"field_team_reference_for_stats_nid","table":"node_data_field_team_reference_for_stats","field":"field_team_reference_for_stats_nid","override":{"button":"Override"},"relationship":"none"}},"fields":{"counter":{"label":"","alter":{"alter_text":0,"text":"","make_link":0,"path":"","link_class":"","alt":"","prefix":"","suffix":"","target":"","help":"","trim":0,"max_length":"","word_boundary":1,"ellipsis":1,"html":0,"strip_tags":0},"empty":"","hide_empty":0,"empty_zero":0,"counter_start":"1","exclude":0,"id":"counter","table":"views","field":"counter","override":{"button":"Override"},"relationship":"none"},"field_season_total_wins_value":{"label":"Wins","alter":{"alter_text":0,"text":"","make_link":0,"path":"","link_class":"","alt":"","prefix":"","suffix":"","target":"","help":"","trim":0,"max_length":"","word_boundary":1,"ellipsis":1,"html":0,"strip_tags":0},"empty":"","hide_empty":0,"empty_zero":0,"link_to_node":0,"label_type":"widget","format":"default","multiple":{"group":true,"multiple_number":"","multiple_from":"","multiple_reversed":false},"exclude":1,"id":"field_season_total_wins_value","table":"node_data_field_season_total_wins","field":"field_season_total_wins_value","override":{"button":"Override"},"relationship":"none"},"field_season_total_losses_value":{"label":"Losses","alter":{"alter_text":0,"text":"","make_link":0,"path":"","link_class":"","alt":"","prefix":"","suffix":"","target":"","help":"","trim":0,"max_length":"","word_boundary":1,"ellipsis":1,"html":0,"strip_tags":0},"empty":"","hide_empty":0,"empty_zero":0,"link_to_node":0,"label_type":"widget","format":"default","multiple":{"group":true,"multiple_number":"","multiple_from":"","multiple_reversed":false},"exclude":1,"id":"field_season_total_losses_value","table":"node_data_field_season_total_losses","field":"field_season_total_losses_value","override":{"
